text.tspan: Delrin is a trade name for POM.
Sculpteo have POM at 2, 3 and 5 mm.
Variation of POM at 2mm is +/-0.26mm (approximated from Ponoko values for 0.8 and 2.3mm).
Argh... Shifting over the top of the joint does mean
the tape can't be wrapped around right at the right edge.
But perhaps I can live with that - first put down the left-to-right
"support" piece of tape and then wrap around top-to-bottom.
You've fixed the issue at the base of the arm. Now the curve hits after the end of the arm.
The slots start at 2.26mm, continue like so for 3mm
